Basically forcing you into the POV of a loser most people are just geared to hate. Some people might be into that but I have a suspicion that most people rather see some development if the MC's gimmick is being a bastard just for the sake of it.

>>59586762
And again, I partially agree with you. Problem is trying to make some Machiavellian sperglord that can manage to be likeable. Someone being likable normally is due to having some "positive" traits, which tends to detract from the whole "obviously" evil part. It's possible but a bit oxymoronic in that they need to have some redeemable traits.
